        "text": "Pamela and Tommy’s relationship was truly whirlwind, and four days after meeting, they married on February 19, 1995.\n\nTheir relationship hit headlines soon after, not just for the speediness of their courtship.\n\nIt was back in headlines when a sex tape of the pair appeared online, after having reportedly been stolen and released in 1995.\n\nThe couple sued the distribution company, Internet Entertainment Group, but this was settled out of court in 1997.\n\nA representative for the couple told CNET at the time of the case’s conclusion: \"In order to protect what privacy they have left, the Lees have entered into a confidential settlement agreement with IEG.\n\nHe reportedly kicked out at his wife, who was holding their son Brandon at the time and was arrested.\n\nTommy pleaded guilty to assaulting his wife and was imprisoned for six months.\n\nAfter his release, there was speculation about the couple reuniting, however this was soon proven to be wrong when they entered into a custody battle for their children.\n\nThere were still signs of a rekindling of their relationship, and in 2008 Pamela moved back in with Tommy, but they split a few months later and she left his home.\n\nSpeaking of her relationship with Tommy, Pamela said: “I have tortured myself over it for years and was devastated and depressed about that relationship."
